In front of the Nobel Peace Center in Oslo. NORWAY.

September 3, 2024 🤍🍉


@aksjonsgruppa.for.palestina  held a protest outside the @nobelpeacecenter. The action was led by women dressed in the traditional Palestinian embroidered dress, thobe, representing Palestinians and Palestinian culture. Behind them were people dressed in black and with bloody hands, representing Israel`s murder of Palestinians and the countries and companies that enable their human rights abuses.

📍Oslo Norway In front of Nobel Peace Center.
 The power of the people✊🏽🇵🇸 against the people in power.
@eyadalzaro 📸
@aksjonsgruppa.for.palestina

📍Oslo Norway ❤️‍🩹🇵🇸 
@eyadalzaro 📸

There’s madness in a world that encourages ignorance and bliss, over a stark reality that has smacked us clean in the face for 10 months. A world that thinks it can go about its business, while loved ones aather the body parts of loved ones in garbage bags. What is a human life worth? Do we all share the same future?

Today, Oslo was reminded of the meaning of the phrase “when words fail.” Thank you to the Freedom Theatre, Nordic Black Xpress, and Crotonicx for the lasting impression your performance left. Thank you to the Palestinian students of Jenin for transcending the forum of theater into our collective desire for a free Palestine.

Performance: WAHA SOS - Significance of Spirit. August 25th 2024. Botsparken in Grønland, Oslo, Norway

