A Norwegian woman suffering from cancer feels sad with the children of Gaza 💔🇵🇸
She says: I cannot say “Ramadan Kareem” without choking on my tears this year. Love and all hope for a peaceful Ramadan from my kitchen and my heart to everyone! But especially for the people of Palestine. You have my heart every day. With the living, and with the dead. Please stop this madness!

Bread Project: She bakes them all into gingerbread, every soul killed in Gaza. Then they placed them one by one outside the Israeli Embassy in Oslo in a silent ritual performance and a freezing atmosphere. I bleed for them, cry for them, scream for them, all that seems right as the events of the genocide unfold. I have lived and breathed it since December 3, 2023, and I will continue until the murders stop. This is my commitment. For life if necessary.

